item.title: Items removed from global objects that can still spawn?
item.dc:creator: @_Rich Rich
item.description:
@_Rich wrote:

[quote=“x0 0wn, post:8, topic:179601”][quote author=X Da Master X link=topic=240804.msg2041056#msg2041056 date=1202561694]
Global objects are the objects u are adding.
So you have default objects on your map(like tree’s,door’s,bankbooth’s,…)
And you have ur GlobalObjects(That are the extra objects)

So the default objects are in the map so u can’t delete them.
You can only delete your own extra objects.

Are u getting what im saying?
[/quote]

Wrong.

Murder, search for deletethatobject in client.java

Then put in the coords of the object you want to delete.[/quote]

Thats only in my source, the regular devolution server 7.0, you have to use ReplaceObject(), or get a addGlobalObject, and deletethatobject voids
